{"type":"message","id":"f219ca95","parentId":"a10f7c2c","timestamp":"2026-04-09T03:05:20.526Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I encountered an issue with fetching AI news articles from the web for you. It seems that `web_search` requires a Brave Search API key, which isn't currently set up in my configuration or environment.\n\nTo resolve this, you can either:\n\n1. **Set the API Key:** You can add your Brave Search API key by running:\n   ```bash\n   openclaw configure --section web\n   ```\n   This will prompt you to enter the API key. Alternatively, you can set it manually in the Gateway environment:\n   ```sh\n   export BRAVE_API_KEY=<your_api_key>\n   ```\n\n2. **Use a Different Function:** Another approach is to use `web_fetch` instead of `web_search`. This function fetches content from URLs and extracts readable text directly, which might be more suitable for your needs.\n\nHere's how you can proceed with `web_fetch`:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"extractMode\": \"text\",\n  \"maxChars\": 2048,\n  \"url\": \"https://www.example.com/ai-news\"\n}\n```\n\nI recommend specifying a URL that provides the latest AI news or focusing on specific topics like LLMs, RL, diffusion models, VLM, and robotics. Once you have an appropriate URL ready, I can fetch and summarize it for you.\n\nLet me know if you'd like to use `web_fetch` instead, and I'll provide a sample request.\n```\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_2ec578a9-804c-476d-97be-7dc056127745","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"extractMode":"text","maxChars":2048,"url":"https://www.example.com/ai-news"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"qwen-local:latest","usage":{"input":8892,"output":339,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":9231,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775703920522}}
