{"type":"message","id":"21563ccd","parentId":"1f5f344d","timestamp":"2026-04-09T03:06:08.459Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I encountered another error attempting to fetch AI news articles from the web using `web_fetch`. It seems that I need a Brave Search API key for this function to work correctly.\n\nLet me set up the Brave Search API key as per the instructions:\n\n1. **Set the API Key:** You can add your Brave Search API key by running:\n   ```bash\n   openclaw configure --section web\n   ```\n   This will prompt you to enter the API key.\n\n2. **Alternatively, Set Environment Variable:** Alternatively, you can set it manually in the Gateway environment:\n   ```sh\n   export BRAVE_API_KEY=<your_api_key>\n   ```\n\nAfter setting up the API key, I'll try fetching AI news articles again using `web_fetch`. If that fails, we might consider looking for other sources or methods to summarize recent AI news.\n\nPlease let me know how you'd like to proceed.\n```\n"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"qwen-local:latest","usage":{"input":9476,"output":186,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":9662,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775703968457}}
